{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Job\uc1\u8217*s Piety and Prosperity

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}In the land of Uz there was a man called Job\uc1\u8211*a man blameless and upright, who feared God and{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}shunned evil. He had a family of seven sons and{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}three daughters: and he owned seven thousandsheep, three thousand camels, five hundred yokeof oxen, five hundred she-asses, and a vast train ofservants, so that he was the richest man in all the{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}East. Now his sons used to hold feast day about,and they would send and invite their three sisters{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}to eat and drink with them; and when the cycleof feasts was over, Job used to send for them andprepare them for worship, rising early and offeringburnt offerings for them all: for \uc1\u8211* said Job\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Perchance my children have sinned
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And cursed God in their heart.And this Job never failed to do.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Heavenly Council. Satan is permitted to test the Quality of Job\uc1\u8217*s Piety

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Now on a certain day the heavenly Beingscame to present themselves before Jehovah, and{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}among them came Satan. Then Jehovah askedSatan where he had come from, and Satan answeredJehovah thus, "From ranging the earth and from{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}walking up and down it." Then Jehovah said toSatan:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"Hast thou noted my servant Job,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That on earth there is none like him\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
A man blameless and upright,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who fears God and shuns evil?"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}To this Satan made answer:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But is it for nothing that Job fears God?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Hast Thou not Thyself fenced him and his house,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And all he possesses on every side?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The work of his hands Thou hast blessed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And his substance abounds in the land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But put forth Thy hand and touch all he possesses,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And assuredly then to Thy face he will curse Thee."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Whereat Jehovah said to Satan:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"See! all he possesses is in thy power,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But lay not thy hand on the man himself."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Then forth Satan went from the presence of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Blows Fall
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Now on a certain day, as his sons and daughtersWere eating and drinking wine in the house of their{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}eldest brother, suddenly a messenger appearedbefore Job with the tidings:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"The oxen were hard at the plough;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the asses were feeding beside them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}When sabeans fell upon them and seized them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The servants they slew with the sword\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Only I alone am escaped to tell thee."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}While he was still speaking, another came and said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
"The fire of God has fallen from heaven,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And burnt to a cinder the sheep and the servants\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Only I alone am escaped to tell thee."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}While he was still speaking, another came and said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"Chaldeans, formed into three bands,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Made a raid on the camels and seized them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The servants they slew with the sword\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Only I alone am escaped to tell thee."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}While he was still speaking, another came and said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"Thy sons and thy daughters were eating and drinking
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
In the house of their eldest brother:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}On a sudden a mighty wind
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
From the other side of the desert
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
came and smote and four sides of the house,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That it fell on the young folk and killed them\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Only I alone am escaped to tell thee."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then Job rose and rent his robe; and, after shaving
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
his head, he threw himself with these words pros-
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
trate upon the ground:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}"Naked came I from my mother\uc1\u8217*s womb,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And naked thither must I return.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Jehovah hath given, Jehovah hath taken:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The name of Jehovah be blessed."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}In all this Job committed no sin, nor did he charge
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
God with unseemly dealing.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Second Council

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Now on a certain day the heavenly Beings cameto present themselves before Jehovah, and amongthem came Satan to present himself before Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Then Jehovah asked Satan where he had come from,and satan answered Jehovah thus, "From rangingthe earth and from walking up and down it."{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then Jehovah said to Satan:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"Hast thou noted my servant Job,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That on earth there is none like him\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
A man blameless and upright,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who fears God and shuns evil?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
And still he clings to his honour\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
In vain hast thou set me on to destroy him."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}To this Satan made answer:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
"Skin for skin;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
All a man\uc1\u8217*s goods will he give for his life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But put forth Thy hand, touch his bone and his flesh
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And assuredly then to Thy face he will curse Thee."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Whereat Jehovah said to Satan:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
"See! he is on thy power,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But take heed that thou spare his life."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Then forth Satan went from the presence of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Second Test

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
And he smote Job from the sole of his foot to the{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}crown of his head with boils so grievous that hetook a potsherd to scratch with; and, as he was{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}sitting among the ashes, his wife said to him:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
"Art thou clinging still to thine honour?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Curse God and die."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But Job said to her:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
"Must thou too speak
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
As a foolish women speak?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
We accept from God what is good:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Shall we not accept what is evil?"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In all this Job was guilty of no sin of speech.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Job\uc1\u8217*s Friends Come to Comfort Him

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}When Job\uc1\u8217*s three friends heard of all the miserythat had come upon him, they travelled each manfrom his own place \uc1\u8211* Eliphaz the Temabite, Bildadthe Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite; for theyhad made a tyrst together to come to condole with{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}him and comfort him. But when they caught aglimpse of him at a distance they did not recognizehim. Then every man of them wept aloud andtore his robe and scattered dust heavenwards upon{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}his head. Then they sat down beside him upon theground seven days and nights, and no one said a wordto him; for they saw that his pain was very great.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Thereafter Job opened his mouth to curse his{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}day, and thus he began:
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 ACT 1

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Job\uc1\u8217*s Lament and Longing for Death

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Perished the day wherein I was born,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the night which announced that a man-child had come.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4a}Utter darkness let that night be,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9b}Looking for light, but finding none.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4b}May God in the heights above ask not after it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4c}And may no beam shine forth upon it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}May darkness and gloom claim it for their own,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And may the thick cloud rest upon it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Black vapours of the day affright it!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And let the thick darkness snatch it away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
May it not be joined to the days of the year,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or enter into the tale of the months.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}As for that night, let it be barren:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
May there never ring through it a cry of joy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Accursed of sorcerers be that day\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Of those that are skilful to stir up Leviathan.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9a}Dark be the stars of its morning twilight,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9c}And never the eyelids of Dawn may it see;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Since it shut not the doors of my mother\uc1\u8217*s womb,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And hid not trouble from mine eyes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Why died I not at my birth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Breathe my last as I came from the womb,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Why on the knees was I welcomed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And why were there breasts to suck?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}For then had I lain down in quiet,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Then had I slept and had rest\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}With kings of the earth and with cousellors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who built stately tombs for themselves,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Or with princes rich in gold,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who had filled their houses with silver.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Like a hidden untimely birth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Like infants that never see light?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}There the wicked cease their tumult,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
There the weary are at rest\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Prisoners at ease together,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Deaf to the taskmaster\uc1\u8217*s voice.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}There the small and the great are alike,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the servants is free from his master.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Why is light given to the wretched,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And life to the bitter in soul,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Such as long for death, but it comes not,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And dig for it more than for treasure,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Who would joy o\uc1\u8217*er a mound of stones,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And rejoice, could they find a grave?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}To the man whose path is obscured,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who is hedged round about by God\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For my bread there comes to me sighing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
My groans are poured out like water.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}For the evil I fear overtakes me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The things that I dread comes upon me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Scarce have I ease or quiet
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or rest, when tumult cometh.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Eliphaz\uc1\u8217*s Comfortable Exhortation and Revelation

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}May we lift up a word unto thee who art fainting,
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
For who has the heart to restrain his speech?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}see! thou hast instructed many,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And strengthened the drooping hands.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Thy words used to set up the stumbling,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And strengthen the tottering knees.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But now that it comes upon thee, thou art faint;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Now that it reaches thyself, thou art terrified.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Is not thy religion thy confidence,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And thy blameless life thy hope?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Bethink thee: has an innocent man ever perished,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or when have the just been cut off?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}It is those who plough wrong and sow trouble
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That reap it: \uc1\u8211* for this have I seen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}By the breath of God they perish,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
At the blast of HIs anger they vanish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The Lion roared, the hoarse lion thundered:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But his young lion\uc1\u8217*s teeth were broken.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}So for lack of prey he perished,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the cubs of the lioness are scattered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Now to me a word came stealing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And mine ear caught a whisper thereof,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}In thoughts from the visions of night,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
When deep sleep falleth on men.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Fear came upon me and trembling,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That made my bones all quake.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Then a breath passed over my face,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The hair of my flesh bristled up.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}There \uc1\u8211* it \uc1\u8211* stood.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I could not tell what it looked like\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
This form before mine eyes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
In the silence I heard a voice say:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}"Can mortal be just before God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or a man clean before his Creator?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}See! He putteth no trust in His servants,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
His angels He chargeth with folly.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}How much more those whose houses are clay,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Whose very foundation is dust,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Who die before the moth,
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Crushed between morning and evening,
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Bruised without any regarding it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Perished for evermore!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The cord of their tent is torn from them:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
They die \uc1\u8211* but without learning wisdom."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}Call now: will any one answer?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
To which of the saints wilt thou turn?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For vexation killeth the fool,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Indignation slayeth the simpleton.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}I have seen a fool taking root,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But his branch became suddenly rotten,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}His children were far from help,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Crushed beyond hope deliverance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The hungry eat up their harvest,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the thirsty draw from their wells.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}For not from the dust riseth ruin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Nor out of the ground springeth trouble;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But man is born unto trouble,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
While the sons of flame soar above it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Were it I, I would seek unto God;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
My cause I would bring before God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Who doeth great things and unsearchable,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Marvellous things without number,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Who bringeth rain over the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And over the fields sendeth water\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Setting the lowly on high,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And lifting the mourners to safety,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Frustrating the plots of the crafty
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And robbing their hands of success,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}So taking the wise in their guile,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That their tortuous plans fail through rashness:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}They feel in the day as in darkness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
At noontide they grope as at night.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}So the needy He saves from the sword,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the poor from the hands of the mighty.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Thus hope is born in the weak,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And iniquity stoppeth her mouth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Happy then the mortal whom God correcteth:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
So spurn no thou the Almighty\uc1\u8217*s chastening.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For He bindeth the wounds He hath made,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And His hands heal the hurt He hath dealt.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}He will save thee in six distresses,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
In seven no evil shall touch thee.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}In famine He frees thee from death,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And in war from the power of the sword.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}From the scourge of tongue thou art safe;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thou shalt fear not the onslaught of ruin.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}At ruin and dearth shalt thou laugh,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the beasts of the field thou shalt fear not.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}For the stones of the earth are thine allies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The beasts of the field are thy friends.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Thou shalt know that thy tent is secure,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thou shalt visit thy fold and miss nothing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Thy seed thou shalt know to be many,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thine offspring as grass of the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Thou shalt come to the grave in thy strength,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
As a sheaf cometh in its season.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}See! this we have searched \uc1\u8211* so it is.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
We have heard it \uc1\u8211* lay thou it to heart.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Job\uc1\u8217*s Denunciation of Hollow Friendship. His Challenge
of God and His Longing to be Gone
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Then Job answered and said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}O could my vexation be carefully weighed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And my misery set in the balance against it!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For it is more heavy than sand of the sea,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And therefore it is that my words are wild.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For the arrows of God Almighty are in me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
My spirit drinketh their fiery poison.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The terrors of God are arrayed against me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7a}My soul refuseth to be at rest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Doth the wild ass bray as he nibbles the grass,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And over their fodder do oxen low?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Can a man eat that which is tasteless and saltless?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Is there any taste in the slime of the yolk?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}O that I might have my request,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That God would grant me the thing that I long for!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}O that God would consent to crush me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
To let His hand loose and cut me off!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}So should I still have this for my comfort\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Leaping for joy amid torture unsparing\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That I had not concealed the words of the Holy One.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}What is my strength, that I should endure?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Or what is mine end, that I should be patient?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Is my strength the strength of stones?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or was I created with flesh of brass?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Behold! I have no help in myself,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the power to achieve is driven from me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}To one who is fainting a friend should be kind,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Even though he forsaketh the fear of Almighty
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But my brethen have dealt like a treacherous torrent,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Like channels that overflow their banks,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Which are turbid because of the ice
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the snow that hides within them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}But, when they are scorched, they vanish:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
In the heat they are quenched from their place.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The caravans bend their course thither,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Go up through the waste, and perish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The caravans of Tema looked out for them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The companies of Sheba kept hoping:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But their confidence brought them to shame;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
When they came to the place, they blushed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Such now have ye proved unto me:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
When ye look on the terror, ye shudder.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Did I ask you to give me a present,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or make me a gift of your substance,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}To rescue me from the foe,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or from hand of the tyrant to free me?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Teach me, and I will be silent;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Show me wherein I have erred.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}How sweet are words that are true!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But when you reprove, what is reproved?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Is it words that ye mean to reprove?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But for winds are the words of despair.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Would ye throw yourselves on the innocent,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or make an assault on your friend?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Now look upon me, I pray you:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I would surely not lie in your face.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}O turn back \uc1\u8211* let there be no injustice:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Turn back, for the right is still mine.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Is my tongue altogether perverted?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Have I lost the sense of wrong?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}Hath man on the earth not a warfare,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
With days like the days of a hireling?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Like a slave that pants for the shadow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
A hireling that longs for his wages,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So empty months are my portion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And wearisome nights mine appointment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I lie down, saying, "When cometh day?"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
When I rise, methinks, "When cometh even?"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I am full of unrest till the dawn.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Worms and clods clothe my flesh;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
My skin grows hard and then breaks.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}My days are more swift than a shuttle;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
They come to an end without hope.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}O remember my life is but breath;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Mine eyes shall see good nevermore.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The eye that now sees me shall see me no more;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thine eyes shall look for me, but I shall be gone.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Like the cloud that is spent and that passeth away,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He that goes down to Sheol shall come up no more.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He shall never come back to his house again,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the place that was his shall know him no more.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}So my mouth I will not restrain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I will utter mine anguish of spirit,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Pour out mine embittered soul.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Am I a sea or a sea-monster,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That upon me Thou settest a watch?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When I look to my couch to comfort me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
To my bed for relief of my sorrow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then Thou scarest me with dreams,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And with visions dost so affright me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}That gladly would I be strangled:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Death itself I spurn in my pain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I would not live for ever:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Let me go, for my days are but breath.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}What is man, that so great Thou dost count him
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And settest Thine heart upon him\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Visiting him every morning,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And testing him moment by moment?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}O when wilt Thou turn Thine eyes from me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And leave me though but for a moment?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}If I sin, how does that harm Thee,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
O Thou who art Watcher of men?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Why dost Thou make me Thy target?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Why burden Thyself with me?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Why not forgive my sin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And pass mine iniquity by?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For now I shall lie in the dust;
\par}

