{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Bildad\uc1\u8217*s Appeal to the Teaching of Tradition

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}And Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}How long wilt thou utter these things\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
These thy blustering windy words?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Is God a perverter of justice?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The Almighty subverter of right?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}If thy children, for sinning against Him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He has left to bear their transgressions,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Yet seek thou thyself unto God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And supplicate the Almighty.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And if thou art pure and upright,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thy righteous abode He will prosper;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And, though thy beginning be slender,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thine end He shall greatly increase.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For inquire thou of past generations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Regard the search of the fathers:\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For we are but dullards of yesterday,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Whose days on the earth are a shadow\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Shall they not give thee instruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And bring forth words out of their heart?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Can the rush shoot high without swamp,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or the reed grow up without water?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}While yet in its freshness, unplucked,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Of all herbs it withers most quickly.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}So end all who put God out of mind.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the hope of the hypocrite dies.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}His confidence is but a thread,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And his trust as the web of a spider.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}He leans on his house, but it stands not:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He grasps, but it cannot endure.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Like a plant is he, fresh in the sunshine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
With suckers that shoot o\uc1\u8217*er the garden.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Its roots are entwined round the well,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
It lays hold of its stone habitation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But when it is ruined, the spot
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Denies having ever beheld it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Thus its course ends in desolation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And out of the dust springs another."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}See! God spurns not an innocent man,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But He will not uphold evildoers.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}He will yet fill thy mouth with laughter
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thy lips with a shout of joy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Thy foes shall be clothed with shame,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And the tent of the wicked shall vanish.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Job\uc1\u8217*s Challenge of Immoral Omnipotence

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}Job answered and said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Yes, truly: I know it is so:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But with God how can man urge his right?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Should He choose to contend against him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He could answer not one in a thousand.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Wise-hearted and strong as He is,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who hath ever successfully braved Him?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Mountains He moves without effort,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He turns them about in His anger.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}He shaketh the earth from her place,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And maketh her pillars shudder.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}He speaks to the sun, and it shines not;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He setteth a seal on the stars.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He strecheth the heavens all alone;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He treadeth the heights of the sea.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}He maketh the Bear and Orion.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The Pleiades and the southern chambers.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He doeth great things and unsearchable,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Marvellous things without number.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Lo! He passes me by all unseen;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Sweeps past \uc1\u8211* but I cannot perceive Him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}He seizeth, and who can prevent Him?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who dare ask Him, "What doest Thou?"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}God will not withdraw His anger;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The helpers of Rahab stooped under Him:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}How much less can I give Him answer,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And choose out my words against Him?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Were I right, I could give Him no answer,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But needs must entreat my Judge.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}If I called, He would give me no answer;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I cannot believe He would listen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}For He Crushes me in a temptest
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
With many a wanton wound.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}He suffers me not to take breath,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But with bitterness He fills me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Is it question of strength? There He is.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or of justice? Then who will implead Him?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Am I right? Still mine own mouth condemns me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Innocent? He proveth me perverse.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Innocent I am \uc1\u8211* but I reck not.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I spurn my life; \uc1\u8217*tis all one.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And therefore it is that I say,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
"He destroyeth both guiltless and guilty."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}When the scourge bringeth sudden death,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The despair of the blameless He mocketh.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}He hath given up the earth to the wicked;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He veileth the face of its judges.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
If it be not He, who then?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}My days are more swift than a runner,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
They flee unillumined by joy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}They glide like the ships of reed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Like an eagle that darts on its prey.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}If I vow to forget my plaint
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And to wear a bright face for a joyless,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}I shudder at all my pains;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I know Thou wilt not hold me guiltless.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}I then am I infallibly guilty,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
So why should I labour in vain?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}For though I wash me with snow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And cleanse my hands with lye,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Thou wouldst plunge me then in the mire,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
So that even my friends would abhor me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Thou art not a man like myself,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
That we come into judgment together.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}O for an umpire between us,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
To lay his hand on us both!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Let Him take but His rod from off me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And affright me no more with His terrors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}And then I would speak unafraid\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
For not such at heart am I.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}In my soul is a loathing of life,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I will let my complaint loose against Him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I will say to God, "Do not condemn me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
But show me the ground of Thy quarrel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}What dost Thou gain from oppressing
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And spurning the work of Thy hands?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Hast Thou then eyes of flesh?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or seest Thou as man seeth?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Are Thy days like the days of mortals,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Or Thy years like the days of man,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}That Thou shouldest seek out my guilt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And make this search for my sin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Though Thou knowest I am not guilty.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And no treachery cleaves to my hand?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Thy hands did fashion and mould me;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And now wilt Thou turn and destroy me?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Remember Thou madest me like clay,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And back to the dust wilt Thou bring me?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Didst Thou not pour me out like milk,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And curdle me after like cheese,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Clothe me with skin and with flesh,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And knit me with bones and with sinews?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Life Thou didst grant me and favour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thy Providence guarded my spirit;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}While this was Thy secret heart,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And this was Thy purpose, I know.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Do I sin? Then Thou dost observe me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And refuse to acquit me of guilt.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Am I wicked? Then woe us me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Just? I dare not lift up my head\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Full of shame and drunken with sorrow.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}If I rise, like a lion Thou huntest me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Working fresh marvels upon me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And bringing new witness against me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Thine anger with me Thou increasest,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thou musterest fresh hosts against me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}O why from the womb didst Thou bring me?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
O why died I not all unseen?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}O to be as though I had not been,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Borne from the womb to the grave!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Are the days of my life not few?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
O leave me to smile a little,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Ere I go to return no more,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
To the land of darkness and gloom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}To the land of murky darkness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Of gloom and utter confusion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Where the very light is as darkness."
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Zophar\uc1\u8217*s Appeal to the Unsearchable Wisdom

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}Then Zophar of Naamah answered and said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Should a voluble man go unanswered,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
A man who but babbles be justified?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Must men hold their peace at thy bragging?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Thy mocking is no one to curb?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Thou maintainest thy way to be pure,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And thyself to be clean in His sight.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But oh that God would speak,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And open His lips against thee,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And show thee the secrets of wisdom\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
How marvellous are her achievements!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For then thou shouldst know that thy guilt
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
God remembers not wholly against thee.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Canst thou find out the deep things of God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or come nigh the Almighty\uc1\u8217*s perfection?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}It is higher than heaven \uc1\u8211* what canst thou?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Deeper than Sheol \uc1\u8211* what knowest thou?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Longer than earth is its measure,
