{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Shall windy words have an end?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
What is it that provokes thee to answer?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I, too, could speak like you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Were your soul in my soul\uc1\u8217*s stead.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I could weave words together about you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And shake my head at you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}I could strengthen you with my mouth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And encourage you with lip-comfort.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}To speak is no check to my pain;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
To keep silence \uc1\u8211* that easeth me nothing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But now He hath wearied and dazed me;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
