{\cf1\f1\fs22 32}Now these three men ceased answering Job,because he was righteous in his own eyes. Then{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}the anger of Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite,of the family of Ram, was kindled; against Jobwas his anger kindled, because he had made himself{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}out to be more righteous than God. But his angerwas kindled against his three friends as well,because they had condemned Job without finding{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}any answer. Now, as they were older, Elihu had{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}waited while they were speaking with Job; but,on seeing that the three men had no answer to offer,Elihu\uc1\u8217*s anger was kindled.
